TITLE: AN IOT ENABLED PREDICTIVE SAFETY SYSTEM FOR UNDERGROUND MINES USING MACHINE LEARNING-BASED HAZARD DETECTION

Underground mining is most hazardous activity due to presence of harmful gases. 
This project aims to predict and detect potential hazards in underground mines.
Various sensors such as SO2, CO, NO2 and MPU6050 accelerometer are used to detect toxic gases.
By using IOT sensors & ML models, we can enhance worker safety and prevent accidents.
